Le Matin, the French-language tabloidlaunched here in February, said it is shutting down itsoperations because it can no longer get financing.    The paper, launched by private investors, was Montreal'sfourth French-language newspaper and was aimed at readers withabove average incomes and educations. It had a dailycirculation of about 20,000 copies.    Le Matin was printed and distributed by (Southam Inc)'sMontreal Gazette newspaper. A Gazette spokesman said hisnewspaper is Le Matin's biggest creditor but he declined toreveal the amount of debt    Acting publisher Jean-Pierre Bordua said the newspaper'sbank blocked its lines of credit after three of the paper'ssenior managers resigned Friday. Reuter&#3;